@startuml
' M2: stereotype `<<include>>` and `<<extend>>` / `<<extends>>` force a
' dashed open arrow regardless of whether the user wrote `-->` (solid)
' or `..>` (dashed). The visible `<<include>>` text stays as a label.
left to right direction
actor User

usecase "Place Order" as Order
usecase "Validate Card" as Validate
usecase "Apply Coupon" as Coupon
usecase "Generate Receipt" as Receipt

User --> Order

' Solid `-->` with stereotype → normalizes to dashed.
Order --> Validate : <<include>>
' Already-dashed `..>` with stereotype — idempotent normalize.
Order ..> Receipt : <<include>>
' `<<extends>>` (plural form PlantUML accepts).
Coupon --> Order : <<extends>>
@enduml
